## 1. Web-Based Course Registration System Design

### üéØ System Features & Architecture

| Component | Description | Technologies |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Frontend (Client-Side)** | User Interface for students (Registration, Viewing, Management). | **HTML5, CSS3 (Bootstrap), JavaScript (React/Vue)** |
| **Backend (Server-Side)** | Handles business logic, security, and data interaction (e.g., prerequisite checks, availability updates). | **Node.js (Express), Python (Django), or Java (Spring)** |
| **Database** | Stores course, student, and registration data. | **PostgreSQL** or **MongoDB** |

### üìù Key Functionality Implementation

* **Prerequisite Checking:** A backend service validates if the student's record meets required prerequisites before allowing registration.
* **Automatic Availability Update:** When a successful registration occurs, the system **atomically** decrements the `$AvailableSeats` counter. If it reaches **0**, the course is automatically flagged as "Full."
* **Client-Side Validation (JavaScript):** JavaScript ensures input fields (like Student ID or Course Code) are correctly formatted and not empty *before* submitting data to the server, improving responsiveness.

---

## 2. JavaScript Validation for a Four-Digit Number

This HTML file includes the required JavaScript logic to validate the four-digit number based on the given rules.

### `number_validator.html`

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Number Validator</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Four-Digit Number Validator</h1>
    <input type="text" id="numberInput" maxlength="4" placeholder="Enter a 4-digit number">
    <button onclick="validateNumber()">Validate</button>
    <p id="message"></p>

    <script>
        function validateNumber() {
            const input = document.getElementById('numberInput').value;
            const messageElement = document.getElementById('message');

            // 1. Basic Check (Length and NaN)
            if (input.length !== 4 || isNaN(input)) {
                messageElement.textContent = "Error: Please enter a valid four-digit number.";
                messageElement.style.color = "red";
                return;
            }

            // 2. No zero as the first digit
            if (input.charAt(0) === '0') {
                messageElement.textContent = "Error: The first digit cannot be zero.";
                messageElement.style.color = "red";
                return;
            }

            // 3. Entered number must be in ascending order of digits
            const d1 = parseInt(input.charAt(0));
            const d2 = parseInt(input.charAt(1));
            const d3 = parseInt(input.charAt(2));
            const d4 = parseInt(input.charAt(3));

            if (d1 < d2 && d2 < d3 && d3 < d4) {
                messageElement.textContent = `Success: The number ${input} is valid!`;
                messageElement.style.color = "green";
            } else {
                messageElement.textContent = "Error: Digits must be in strict ascending order (e.g., 1234, not 1123 or 4321).";
                messageElement.style.color = "red";
            }
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
